question: I just saw this captain marvel post with over 70,000 notes, and then I noticed that you were the original poster! Lol that's crazy, were you expecting that post to be so popular?
answer:
I thought it’d be a funny post, and maybe if people agreed then it might get like maybe close to 1000 notes like some of my other crack posts. Or maybe several thousand like my post about Brie previously working as a DJ.

TBH the couple months of notifications for that post kinda made me sick of it. Now when I see the post I’m like “eh…” because it just seems like Brie keeps doing phenomenally gayer and gayer shit lols

But initially it was a rollercoaster, because the snowflake red pill MRA types (dudebros and dudegals alike) got all defensive about it, and I was seeing all these notifications lols.

It’s almost a kind of meta-commentary for the whole snowflake red pill MRAs outrage response to Brie and the Captain Marvel movie, because they definitely made noise on that post, but the sheer number of likes really dwarfed the outrage at the end of the day. Just like in real life.

summary:
Me: There was a lady next to me who bought at least 20 copies of Captain Marvel.
My Mom: That’s such a waste and makes no...
body:
Me: There was a lady next to me who bought at least 20 copies of Captain Marvel.

My Mom: That’s such a waste and makes no sense.

Oh, I’m sorry. Not everyone can afford to buy their own copy. Not everyone could afford to see the movie in theater. Not everyone can afford to do both. This lady is allowing others the opportunity to watch a badass superhero whenever they please. This lady decided that she was going to spend hundreds of her own money just to allow others who do not have the means to buy even one copy. She is the good we need in this world, don’t question her actions or claim that her actions make no sense.
